    "objectID": "introduction.html",
    "href": "introduction.html",
    "title": "1  General introduction",
    "section": "",
    "text": "Luxembourg\nBiodiversity citizen science, specifically the huge amount of photo-based contributions to data collection, has greatly accelerated our ability to document diversity and distribution of many taxa, and has helped to achieve thousands of research projects [@REF1].\nLuxembourg is the top country for citizen science activity on iNaturalist after correcting for country size and population [@REF2]. The MNHNL hosts a national XXX antennae, and pushes the use of citizen science platforms such as Observation.org and Naturalist.LU The MNHNL is also active in promoting events making heavy use of such platforms to both experienced naturalists and the public such as Biodiversity Day, and the City Nature Challenge. Such events have been shown to lead to useful and massive contributions [@REF3], but it is also the case in Luxembourg where both observations and identifications are stimulated. For example, several first national records were made during the City Nature Challenge: XXX.",
    "crumbs": [
      "<span class='chapter-number'>1</span>  <span class='chapter-title'>General introduction</span>"
    ]
  },
