    "title": "1  General introduction",
    "section": "Hoverflies in Luxembourg",
    "text": "Hoverflies in Luxembourg\nIn Luxembourg, biodiversity citizen science has greatly contributed to our effort to document the distribution of hoverflies. Despite being only % of all research-grade observations (georeferenced, dated, photographic proof, community agreement on the identification), and being only XXX% of all records available to us, biodiversity citizen science has led to first national records, that is considering every other possible source. Spilomyia manicata (pageXXX ; https://www.inaturalist.lu/observations/233984507) was first observed by Sam Schaack in August 2024 in the south of the country, and identified by himself, Hinatea Ariey, a user named “sirhck”, and Juliette Pfeiffer.\nFigure XXX",
